Figure 2 presents a detailed interfacial analysis of the internal polarizations, energy band and the induced 2DEG at the local AlGaN/AlN/GaN heterojunction. The lattice-resolved HAADF-STEM image (Fig. 2a) indicates the superior crystal quality and that the thickness of AlN is 1.5 nm. The AlN layer not only provides a barrier to strengthen the locality of the 2DEG in triangular potential wells, but also reduces 2DEG scattering by AlGaN. Figure 2b, c shows the atomic model and schematic band structure of the AlGaN/AlN/GaN heterojunction. Owing to the asymmetric lattice structure of the wurtzite materials, spontaneous polarization in AlGaN and GaN layer was formed, denoted as PspAlGaN\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
