				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{{{\text{piezo}}}}$$\end{document} and the intrinsic Psp\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{{{\text{sp}}}}$$\end{document} and Plm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{{{\text{lm}}}}$$\end{document} were demonstrated in detail to systematically explain the intrinsic mechanism. This study provides an in-depth understanding of the piezotronic-effect and endeavors to open new ways for thermal management, with practical applications in flexible electronics.
